            There are vast rural areas in the South Downs&#x2014;Lewes and Eastbourne are obviously specific towns&#x2014;in which people have to use their motor cars. The report that the Government produced yesterday confirms that dependency on cars in rural areas is greater than that in urban areas. We ignore such realities at our peril because that leads to increased congestion, more accidents and danger on the roads, and more damage to the economies of the areas served by those highways. I totally reject the strategy of the Liberal Democrats.</p><p>
